%% Diagram: Resource Discovery Order for LCP Images
%% Type: sequence
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant B as Browser
    participant N as Network (HTTP/2)
    participant S as Server

    U->>B: Navigate
    B->>S: GET /index.html
    S-->>B: HTML stream
    B->>B: Preload scanner reads <link rel=preload> + <img>
    par LCP image (fetchpriority=high)
        B->>N: GET hero.avif (priority: HIGH)
    and Other above-fold assets
        B->>N: GET hero.css (priority: HIGH)
        B->>N: GET app.js (priority: HIGH)
    and Below-fold lazy images
        B-->>B: Hold loading=lazy candidates
    end
    N->>S: Multiplexed streams
    S-->>N: Bytes (hero.avif streamed first)
    N-->>B: hero.avif decoded sync
    B-->>U: Paint LCP element
    Note over B,N: Lazy images stay queued until\nIntersectionObserver fires
